
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `lpr` baraye chap kardane file-ha estefade mishavad. Yani yek file ra mifreste be printer ta chap shavad.  

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `lpr filename` --> 🖨️ Chap kardane yek file ba name `filename`.
    🔹 `lpr -P printername filename` --> 🎯 Chap kardane file ba estefade az yek printer khass ba name `printername`.
    🔹 `lpr -# numcopies filename` --> 🔢 Chap kardane `numcopies` copy az file.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**
    
    $ lpr document.txt
    
    🔹 Chap kardane file `document.txt` ba printer pishfarz.

    $ lpr -P hplaserjet report.pdf
    
    🔹 Chap kardane file `report.pdf` ba printeri ke name aan `hplaserjet` ast.

✅ **Mesal sade:**
    
    $ lpr -# 2 resume.txt
    
    🔹 Chap kardane 2 copy az file `resume.txt` ba printer pishfarz.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `lpr` command is used to print files. It sends a file to the printer to be printed.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `lpr filename` --> 🖨️ Prints the file named `filename`.
    🔹 `lpr -P printername filename` --> 🎯 Prints the file using a specific printer named `printername`.
    🔹 `lpr -# numcopies filename` --> 🔢 Prints `numcopies` copies of the file.

🛠 **Examples:**
    
    $ lpr document.txt
    
    🔹 Prints the `document.txt` file using the default printer.

    $ lpr -P hplaserjet report.pdf
    
    🔹 Prints the `report.pdf` file using the printer named `hplaserjet`.

✅ **Simple Example:**
    
    $ lpr -# 2 resume.txt
    
    🔹 Prints 2 copies of the `resume.txt` file using the default printer.

